title: Oktoberfest moved to... November
text:
Organisers move Oktoberfest to November at Elwick Racecourse by: What are these? Oktoberfest organiser Stuart Harris. Source: News Corp Australia 
LESS than a week before Hobart beer festival Oktoberfest was due to be held, organisers have announced the event has moved to November and will be held at Elwick Racecourse. 
The annual festival was scheduled to take place this Saturday, with more than 2500 tickets already sold. 
The event was scheduled to be held at Princes Wharf 1 until a row with the Hobart City Council over the supply of tables and chairs last month organiser Stuart Harris was forced to find an alternate venue in Glenorchy. 
“After running a hugely successful Oktoberfest at Geelong Racecourse two weeks ago we realised that a park-style event makes for a much better Oktoberfest,” Mr Harris said.
